The video is a piece of 'experimental artwork', different types of video effects between cuts from one song to another.



INFO:
--------
'The Value of Ignorance' is taken from a live recording on June 3rd 1988 at The Dominion Theatre in London and 'The Year of The Horse' was recorded over two nights in October 1990 at the Forest National in Brussels and Ahoysportpaleis in Rotterdam. Full Description 'The Value of Ignorance' mostly covers material from O'Connor's sensational 1987 debut album The Lion & the Cobra, where she synthesized her influences into her own ethereal, atmospheric sound, enveloped in tortured passion.
